OSAGE OIL AND REFINING COMPANY v. CONTINENTAL OIL COMPANY. No. 240. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 18, 1930. J. E. Whitehead, of Dallas, Tex., for appellant. Ray S. Fellows, of Tulsa, Okl., for appellee.

Before LEWIS, COTTERAL, and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed June 18, 1930, at appellant’s costs, on motion of appellee.
